  <front>
   <head>PALLAS and VENUS. AN EPIGRAM.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Swain had judg'd the great Dispute;</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And Beauty's Pow'r obtain'd the Golden Fruit;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">When , loose in all Her naked Charms,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Met  great Daughter clad in shining Arms.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The wanton Goddess view'd the Warlike Maid</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">From Head to Foot, and Tauntingly She said:</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Yield, Sister; Rival, yield; Naked, You see,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">I vanquish: Guess how Potent I should be;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">If to the Field I came in Armour drest;</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Dreadful, like Thine, my Shield, and terrible my Crest.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The Warrior Goddess with Disdain reply'd;</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thy Folly, Child, is equal to thy Pride:</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Let a brave Enemy for once advise,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And  (if 'tis possible) be Wise.</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thou to be strong must put off every Dress:</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thy only Armour is thy Nakedness:</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And more than once, (or Thou art much bely'd)</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">By  himself That Armour has been try'd.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
